  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0baf \u0baa\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf 11 \u0bb5\u0baf\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "An 11-year-old boy died due to electric shock in Wellawaya area",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Wellawaya Police said that an 11-year-old boy was electrocuted while playing at a relative's house in Wellawaya Kottaveheragala area.",
        "The police said that a boy named RM Nuvan Netsara, who was studying in standard 6, died in this way.",
        "It is reported that the boy who died while playing at his relative's house got caught in the electric wire placed near the broom and died."
      ],
